      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>As few year back I asked myself the simple question “can I <strong>learn to hypnotize someone</strong>” and I found that the rabbit hole goes very deep. By the time I learned the answer I had been through a lot of adventures and even started my own hypnosis websites!</p>
<div style="padding: 5px; float: right;"><a title="Learn to Hypnotize Someone" href="http://www.ehypnosisinduction.com/course" target="_blank"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4091/5187627879_63fb29a904_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Learn to Hypnotize Someone" width="240" height="135" title="Learn to Hypnotize Someone    Is This Mind Control?" /></a><br />
<small>credit: <a title="opensourceway" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/47691521@N07/5187627879/" target="_blank">opensourceway</a></small></div>
<p>As first I was just interested but then I started to read more and more and found out that if I could learn to hypnotize people without them knowing I could influence a lot of situations in my life and start to get what I want more quickly</p>
<p>Not that I wanted to learn mind control at first, it was just that I needed to be more persuasive and less of a wimp.</p>
<p>WHAT IS HYPNOSIS?</p>
<p>This is the first thing I learn and I was surprise to find out that people are hypnotize all the time. It’s just a state of mind where the hypnotists can bypass the critical mind and talk direct to the subconscious. This is used a lot in advertising and is why some adverts seem so attractive.</p>
<p>So there is nothing to fear from hypnosis, you are just using the same power that people go through every day when they fall into a day dream of loose track of time.</p>
<p>Have you every got home from work and wondered where the day went?</p>
<p>You where in a hypnotic state the whole time and didn&#8217;t even know it!</p>
<h2>Learn to Hypnotize Someone In 3 Steps</h2>
<p>LET’S GET INTO SOME TACTICS.</p>
<p>1. The first thing you need to do is to be able to look at a person very closely. Notice their heart beat and how flushed their face looks. All these clues will tell you how deeply in trance that person is at the moment. (We are all in a certain stage of trance.)</p>
<p>2. You must gain a strong rapport with a person before they will let you hypnotize them. You need to treat the person like family or your best friend. Look deep into their eyes and smile. All this will help you build rapport.</p>
<p>3. Now the final step is the hypnotic scripts. I spent months trying to work out what to say to put a person under and then I discovered a whole world of scripts that have been proven to work every time. All you need to do is hop onto YouTube and find the self hypnosis videos with the most hits (There are 1000’s of them). Then you just copy the script word for word when you are hypnotizing a person.</p>
<p>Final thoughts.</p>
<p>I hope you enjoyed this shortcut to <em>Learn to Hypnotize Someone</em>, I believe that if you want to learn something fast you just need to model the “best” and that is exactly what I have done with this simple method.</p>
